HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 761
By Hemmer
A RESOLUTION to recognize John Bradley, Senior Vice
President, Economic Development of the
Tennessee Valley Authority on the occasion of
his retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should honor those citizens who have performed
with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their years of industry; and
WHEREAS, John Bradley is one such estimable person, who has served with distinction
since 2002 as Senior Vice President, Economic Development of the Tennessee Valley Authority
(TVA), and will soon be taking his much-deserved retirement from the nation's largest public
utility; and
WHEREAS, a proud resident of the Volunteer State, John Bradley grew up in Memphis
and attended the University of Tennessee, Knoxville; and
WHEREAS, a veteran economic development professional with over thirty-five years'
experience, John Bradley served as the Senior Vice President of Economic Development at the
Memphis Regional Chamber of Commerce prior to his employment by TVA; and
WHEREAS, during his tenure at TVA, Mr. Bradley implemented a wide range of
impactful initiatives, including a targeted recruitment program and enhanced support for
community development and existing industries; and
WHEREAS, he helped create the TVA Certified Megasite Program, which earned TVA
the Gold Excellence Award in Economic Development from the International Economic
Development Council; and
WHEREAS, under his leadership, TVA Economic Development has contributed to the
creation of more than 489,000 new jobs, the retention of 802,000 jobs, and a total capital
investment of over $150 billion across the Tennessee Valley; his impactful work furthered TVA's
HJR0761
010976
- 1 -

mission of service to help improve the quality of life for the ten million residents of the Valley
region; and
WHEREAS, no stranger to awards and accolades, John Bradley has been recognized
for leading one of the top economic development teams in the country, as TVA has been
honored as a Top Utility in Economic Development by Site Selection magazine for twenty
consecutive years and has been named one of Nashville Business Journal's Best Places to
Work; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Bradley has played a key role in shaping the careers of countless
economic development professionals through his support, mentorship, and world-class sense of
humor; and
WHEREAS, this esteemed gentleman has been mistaken for Little Jimmy Dickens's
grandson and is known for being the life of the party, never missing an opportunity to crack a
joke; and
WHEREAS, a semi-professional wine connoisseur, Mr. Bradley also enjoys the beach
and fishing and plans to spend his retirement at his cabin, fishing, traveling, and spending more
time with his family; and
WHEREAS, John Bradley exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community
that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, throughout his estimable career, John Bradley has demonstrated the utmost
professionalism, ability, and integrity; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we extend to John Bradley our heartfelt wishes for a happy and fulfilling
retirement and every continued success in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
